wiki.summary: "TV" is about accepting responsibility for a failing relationship. The protagonist chooses to avoid their feelings by escaping into the distraction of television, yet they struggle with the guilt of leaving behind the people they used to be with. Even when they try to fix the relationship, they come to the realization that the problem lies within them. In the end, they accept responsibility for the issues and come to the conclusion that they are the problem. Read more on Last.fm.
